text:
Teclast TL-C300 usb media player not properly recognized. Failed to create /dev entry on plugin and froze startup if present during boot. Found to require 2 quirks:- NO_TEST_UNIT_READY | NO_SYNCHRONIZE_CACHE

Also - no usbdevs entries for Emtec 2GB memory stick or Mustek DV5000 camera

Fix: 

Following mods for usbdevs & umass.c:-

usbdevs:-

/*### added for Teclast TL-C300 media player support */
vendor TECLAST          0x071b  Teclast
/* Teclast products */
product TECLAST TLC300          0x3203  USB Media Player

/*### added for Emtec 2GB memory stick support */
vendor EMTEC            0x13fe  Emtec 2GB memory stick
/* EMTEC products */
product EMTEC MEMORYSTICK2GB    0x1e00  Emtec 2GB memory stick


umass.c:-

        /*### added for Teclast TL-C300 media player support */
        { USB_VENDOR_TECLAST, USB_PRODUCT_TECLAST_TLC300, RID_WILDCARD,
          UMASS_PROTO_SCSI | UMASS_PROTO_BBB,
          NO_TEST_UNIT_READY | NO_SYNCHRONIZE_CACHE
        },
